articles.title: SpaceX launches NASA’s TEMPO air quality monitoring instrument - The Indian Express
articles.description: NASA's TEMPO instrument is a payload on the Intelsat 40E satellite and will monitor air quality across North America.
articles.content: NASAs high-resolution air pollution monitoring instrument TEMPO lifted atop a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket from the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida at 10 AM IST on Friday.The Tropospheric Emi… [+1982 chars]
